# Firmware Structure

The firmware is organized into several key components:

## Core Components
- [firmware/src/main.cpp](mdc:firmware/src/main.cpp) - Main entry point and setup
- [firmware/src/Emulator/](mdc:firmware/src/Emulator/) - ZX Spectrum emulation core
- [firmware/src/TFT/](mdc:firmware/src/TFT/) - Display handling
- [firmware/src/AudioOutput/](mdc:firmware/src/AudioOutput/) - Audio output management
- [firmware/src/AYSound/](mdc:firmware/src/AYSound/) - AY sound chip emulation
- [firmware/src/Input/](mdc:firmware/src/Input/) - Input handling (keyboard, controllers)
- [firmware/src/Files/](mdc:firmware/src/Files/) - File system operations (SD card, flash)

## ROM and Game Files
- [firmware/data/](mdc:firmware/data/) - Contains ROM files and games if not using SD card

## Configuration
- [firmware/platformio.ini](mdc:firmware/platformio.ini) - Board configurations and pin assignments
